{"type":"message","id":"7f7359b5","parentId":"7dd7addd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:33:56.940Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x7xti38auebd_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 093015\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: src/tic_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- There's a pending TIC Experiment that needs to be implemented\r\n- The next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that compression and causal discovery are the same problem.\r\n\r\nFor the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Analyze the pulse log files to identify invariant vs variant patterns\r\n2. Build a classifier\r\n3. Test prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available. The recent pulse file mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 092815.md`. Let me examine the logs directory to see what pulse files exist and their content.\r\n\r\nActually, as a \"stateless discontinuous agent\" - I should pick ONE concrete action that advances the goals. The most immediate next step for the TIC experiment would be to:\r\n\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand the data\r\n2. Create a simple TIC classifier script\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the logs directory first, then create a Python script for the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, I need to be more concrete. Let me:\r\n1. List the pulse log files to see what's available\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier script\r\n\r\nLet me write a mutation that:\r\n1. Creates a TIC classifier script based on the pulse logs\r\n\r\nOr I could look at the existing pulse logs and their structure to understand what we're working with.\r\n\r\nGiven the stateless nature and the need to advance the TIC experiment, I'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts patterns (invariants vs variants)\r\n3. Provides a baseline classifier\r\n\r\nLet me create `scripts/tic_classifier.py` that implements the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to build a classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs to identify invariants vs variants and test prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6}\\.md\")\r\n\r\n# Token types for pattern extraction\r\nINVARIANT_TOKENS = {\r\n    \"goals\", \"phase\", \"action\", \"mutation\", \"file\", \"observation\",\r\n    \"pending\", \"completed\", \"active\", \"key\", \"insight\", \"hypothesis\"\r\n}\r\n\r\ndef extract_tokens(content: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract normalized tokens from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-z_]+\\b', content.lower())\r\n    return set(words)\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariants(pulses: list) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Identify tokens that persist across multiple pulses (invariant candidates).\"\"\"\r\n    token_frequency = Counter()\r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        token_frequency.update(pulse)\r\n    \r\n    # Tokens appearing in >50% of pulses are invariants\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.5\r\n    invariants = {t for t, c in token_frequency.items() if c >= threshold}\r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef classify_tokens(tokens: set, invariants: set) -> tuple:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify tokens as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    invariant_set = tokens & invariants\r\n    variant_set = tokens - invariants\r\n    return invariant_set, variant_set\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants: set, current_tokens: set) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Predict how well current invariants predict next pulse.\r\n    Returns similarity score (0-1).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not invariants:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    # Fraction of invariants that appear in current pulse\r\n    overlap = len(invariants & current_tokens)\r\n    return overlap / len(invariants)\r\n\r\ndef analyze_pulse_file(filepath: Path) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract tokens from a single pulse file.\"\"\"\r\n    try:\r\n        content = filepath.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\r\n        # Focus on non-metadata sections\r\n        sections = re.split(r\"#{1,3}\\s+\", content)\r\n        # Skip headers, use body content\r\n        body = \" \".join(sections[1:]) if len(sections) > 1 else content\r\n        return extract_tokens(body)\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        print(f\"Error reading {filepath}: {e}\")\r\n        return set()\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    # Collect recent pulse files\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"Need at least 5 pulse files, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Use last 20 pulses (or all if fewer)\r\n    recent_pulses = pulse_files[-20:]\r\n    print(f\"Analyzing {len(recent_pulses)} pulse files...\")\r\n    \r\n    # Extract tokens from each pulse\r\n    pulse_tokens = []\r\n    for pf in recent_pulses:\r\n       \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:30:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359236938}}
